text:
Oh, boy bro. You don't know what this video has done to me.

I am in the gym listening to your video while exercising and your video triggered my trauma (PTSD), the memories of exploitation I had gone through during my job came to me. 

I have to stop the exercise, stop your video. Have to play some songs. 

The point you said during your video is "all people have the same brain." I am sorry bro, but you are so wrong about that. 

Every person will not have the same brain or the same amount of intelligence. If that will see 10s of Einsteins every generation. But no, we see only 1 Einstein every 100 years. 

Intelligence/genius depends on various factors like genetics, nutrition while growing up, nutrition while in the mother's womb, not taking any wrong meds during the mother being pregnant, attention and childhood the child got during childhood if gone through any trauma during childhood etc. 

Take me as an example. I like writing stories and thinking about criticism. But I am a failure at education. I failed BTech. Even if Einstein takes tuition for me I will not pass Engineering Mathematics-1 and 2. Because I don't get them. 

But I can see any small flaw in editing or VFX mistakes just like that. Because I grew up watching films, I like stories.

Because my mom had gone through a lot of trauma. She used to make me sit in front of the tv and I used to just watch tv. (Until 5 years old.) 
That is why after joining the school I felt like using the brain felt too much, so always used to get only 70% marks.

In the other case my cousin. His mom is so interactive with him. She used to make him play puzzles like word-building from a very small age. She always used to entertain him and be interactive with him and used to buy video games from a small age. 

Now he studied in Bits Pilani, did Ms in the USA and got a job in Google. 

You cannot plant a crop and leave it there and except veggies from it. You have to supply water, spray pesticides, manage if other creepers are coming around it. 

If you don't do all of them correctly. The tree won't be good.
